t with family and is especially interesting to children. Eco Cave Garden was created to provide tourists with a view of Himalayan wildlife's natural environment by creating various curves for different animals to return home. The Eco Cave Garden is about 1 kilometre from Mall Road and easily accessible on foot. Otherwise, you may take a taxi. 2. Mall Road The British built Nainital's Mall Road, formally known as Govind Ballabh Pant Marg. The Nainital Mall Road connects the hill town of Mallital with the two ends of Tallital, the primary shopping, eating, and cultural centre of wonder in Nainital. There are several hotels, showrooms, department stores, and businesses on Mall Road. Restaurants and cafes are available. Mall Road is home to some of the greatest hotels and restaurants in Nainital. During the day, it is one of the busiest and most crowded locations. A night walk around the mall has its special beauty, with the cold wind coming across the road through the lake. It is a famous tourist location with a wonderful view of Nainital Lake. An interesting fact about this location is that it was used to film several famous Bollywood movies, including "Kati Patang" and "Koi Mil Gaya". It is one of the most popular tourist attractions in Nainital. 3. Tiffin Top Tiffin Top, also known as Dorothy's Seat, is a well-known tourist attraction in Nainital. This is a wonderful picnic area to enjoy a beautiful view of Nainital. Cher, Oak, and Deodar trees cover the beautiful Tiffin Top. When viewed from here, the Naini Lake and the Kumaon hills are lovely. Tiffin Top was called for the restaurant at the top of the hill, Dorothy's Seat. On clear days, the amazing view of Nanda Devi may also be viewed. Tiffin Top's wonderful view makes it an ideal place for an adventurous journey. The surrounding peaks of the Aryapatta hills and the lovely landscape of Nainital make it a popular destination for both residents and visitors. Dorothy Kellett, an English painter who used to sit and 